"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunktaskforge_docs=globalThis.webpackChunktaskforge_docs||[]).push([[8271],{3032:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"v1-release","metadata":{"permalink":"/Docusaurus-Documentation-Practice-Projects/blog/v1-release","editUrl":"https://github.com/missionshrestha/Docusaurus-Documentation-Practice-Projects/tree/main/blog/2025-01-10-v1-release.mdx","source":"@site/blog/2025-01-10-v1-release.mdx","title":"TaskForge v1.0.0-beta Release","description":"Our first public beta release of TaskForge with CLI, API, and config improvements.","date":"2025-01-10T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/Docusaurus-Documentation-Practice-Projects/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"changelog","permalink":"/Docusaurus-Documentation-Practice-Projects/blog/tags/changelog"},{"inline":true,"label":"cli","permalink":"/Docusaurus-Documentation-Practice-Projects/blog/tags/cli"},{"inline":true,"label":"api","permalink":"/Docusaurus-Documentation-Practice-Projects/blog/tags/api"}],"readingTime":1.26,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Alex Rivera","title":"Founder, TaskForge","socials":{},"key":null,"page":null},{"name":"TaskForge Team","socials":{},"key":null,"page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"TaskForge v1.0.0-beta Release","description":"Our first public beta release of TaskForge with CLI, API, and config improvements.","authors":[{"name":"Alex Rivera","title":"Founder, TaskForge"},{"name":"TaskForge Team"}],"tags":["release","changelog","cli","api"],"slug":"v1-release"},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Welcome to TaskForge","permalink":"/Docusaurus-Documentation-Practice-Projects/blog/welcome"}},"content":"Today we\'re excited to ship **TaskForge v1.0.0-beta**\u2014our first public beta release.\\n\\nThis release focuses on solidifying the core experience: projects, tasks, CLI, and API.\\n\\n## Highlights\\n\\n- \ud83e\uddf0 New `taskforge init` flow with clearer prompts\\n- \u2705 Improved task listing and filtering in the CLI\\n- \ud83d\udd10 API authentication and rate limiting now enabled by default\\n- \u2699\ufe0f Structured `taskforge.config.json` with environments support\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\n:::warning\\nThis beta includes a breaking change to the way `projectId` is handled in\\n`taskforge.config.json`. If you previously edited `projectId` by hand, please read the\\n[Config File](/docs/reference/config-file) docs carefully before upgrading.\\n:::\\n\\n- Projects created with older previews may need to be reinitialized.\\n- The CLI now refuses to run if `projectId` is missing or mismatched.\\n\\n## API updates\\n\\n- All endpoints are now served from `https://api.taskforge.dev/v1`.\\n- Rate limits are enforced at `100 requests/minute` per API key.\\n- Error responses include consistent `error` and `message` fields.\\n\\nSee the [API Overview](/docs/reference/api-overview) for details and `curl` examples.\\n\\n## CLI updates\\n\\n- `taskforge task add` now accepts `--assignee` and `--due` flags.\\n- `taskforge task list` adds a `--status` filter.\\n- `taskforge --config` lets you point to a specific config file.\\n\\nCheck out the [CLI Usage](/docs/guides/cli-usage) guide to see all available commands.\\n\\n## What\'s next\\n\\nOver the coming weeks we\'ll be focusing on:\\n\\n- Smoother onboarding for new teams\\n- Deeper integrations with CI providers\\n- More examples and templates in the docs\\n\\nIf you try the beta, we\'d love your feedback. Reach out via the [Contact](/contact) page\\nand tell us how TaskForge fits into your workflow."},{"id":"welcome","metadata":{"permalink":"/Docusaurus-Documentation-Practice-Projects/blog/welcome","editUrl":"https://github.com/missionshrestha/Docusaurus-Documentation-Practice-Projects/tree/main/blog/2025-01-01-welcome.mdx","source":"@site/blog/2025-01-01-welcome.mdx","title":"Welcome to TaskForge","description":"Introducing TaskForge, a developer-first project management platform.","date":"2025-01-01T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"announcement","permalink":"/Docusaurus-Documentation-Practice-Projects/blog/tags/announcement"},{"inline":true,"label":"product","permalink":"/Docusaurus-Documentation-Practice-Projects/blog/tags/product"},{"inline":true,"label":"beta","permalink":"/Docusaurus-Documentation-Practice-Projects/blog/tags/beta"}],"readingTime":0.49,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"TaskForge Team","title":"TaskForge Product & Engineering","url":"https://facebook.com/@taskforge","image_url":"/img/favicon.ico","imageURL":"/Docusaurus-Documentation-Practice-Projects/img/favicon.ico","socials":{},"key":null,"page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Welcome to TaskForge","description":"Introducing TaskForge, a developer-first project management platform.","authors":[{"name":"TaskForge Team","title":"TaskForge Product & Engineering","url":"https://facebook.com/@taskforge","image_url":"/img/favicon.ico","imageURL":"/img/favicon.ico"}],"tags":["announcement","product","beta"],"slug":"welcome"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"TaskForge v1.0.0-beta Release","permalink":"/Docusaurus-Documentation-Practice-Projects/blog/v1-release"}},"content":"Happy New Year\u2014and welcome to **TaskForge** \ud83c\udf89\\n\\nTaskForge is a project management platform designed specifically for developers\\nand technical teams. Instead of forcing you into a UI-only workflow, TaskForge\\nmeets you where you already work:\\n\\n- A clean, minimal web dashboard\\n- A powerful CLI for automation\\n- A simple, well-documented REST API\\n\\nWith TaskForge you can:\\n\\n- Spin up new projects in seconds\\n- Manage tasks from your terminal or CI\\n- Keep your team aligned without leaving your dev tools\\n\\nIf you\'re curious to try it out, start with the [Quickstart](/docs/quickstart)\\nand create your first project today."}]}}')}}]);